24/05/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Cabinet spokesman Theodoros Roussopoulos said Monday (23 May) that last week's visit of Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis to Washington was very successful. At a news conference, Roussopoulos noted US President George W. Bush's call for a "strategic partnership" between the United States and Greece. Athens also welcomed Bush's statement praising bilateral co-operation and Greece's role in regional and international issues. (ANA, MPA - 23/05/05)
